[00:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The videos you\'re watching right now may seem a little familiar in their content because of course they\'re based on the old Sora AI video generator prompts that we\'ve seen for oh a year or so, but it\'s not Sora you\'re looking at. It\'s not'

[00:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Veo-2. It\'s not Kling. It\'s not Runway. It\'s probably not any of the ones you\'re thinking of. Welcome back to the channel where we discuss the creative uses of AI and you are looking at the Vedu new Q1 model. And I got to say it\'s pretty'

[00:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'incredible. Now, there are so many advancements being made in AI generated video right now that it\'s impossible to say this is the best one, but it\'s definitely one to watch and we\'re going to dig into it right now. If you are'

[00:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unfamiliar with Vedu, it\'s long been one of my favorite platforms. I just love what it does with motion in their videos that they generate and the Q1 model has taken it to a whole new level. And you\'ve seen examples of the realism and the sharpness and the color and these'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'are all 1080p videos that it\'s creating and it works with both text to video and image to video including start and end frames. The Q1 model is not the only model available on the platform. You also have their version 2.0, 1.5 and 1.0'

[01:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'version in some cases. Although there\'s really no reason to go back to version one. The platform offers text to video as I mentioned, image to video, reference to video which we\'ll go over in detail and a new feature AI sound'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'effect which takes the ability to automatically add sound effects to your video to a whole new level with timelines and precision placement of the sound. They\'ve also added what they call templates and you\'ve probably seen all kinds of examples from various platforms'

[01:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that offer this type of functionality and they have included it here as well. I hope you got a few minutes because I\'m going to show you several examples of all of these things and show you how to use them. Let\'s start with text to video. Now, the first thing you\'re going'

[01:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to do is choose the model. We\'re going to choose the Vedu Q1 beta model right now and then down here in the settings we can go with the general style which is for more photorealistic videos and then the animation style if you have'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'illustrations, anime, or anything like that. Currently, with the Q1 model, we have a duration limit of 5 seconds and only 1080p video output. We can adjust the movement amplitude, how much movement is going to occur in the video.'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I would encourage you not to just always go with auto assuming that it\'s going to make the best choice because you can get a wide range of results if you change from small, medium, to large. Of course, you\'ve got your aspect ratio and the number of generations you want and the'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'amount of videos you can generate at a time up to four. As far as generating the video, pretty self-explanatory. You\'d enter the prompt up in this area here and click on create. And in about 5 minutes, I\'ve found with the Q1 model,'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you get your results. I\'m going to show you a few examples that I\'ve used using text-to-video on the platform. This the prompt was a blonde woman sitting alone in a cozy coffee shop wearing a warm sweater, etc. Here\'s the full-resolution version of this. There\'s an exorbitant'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'amount of steam, but we\'ve got very realistic movement. There\'s absolutely no tearing or artifacting of any kind anywhere. Here, I just changed the prompt slightly, a blonde ogre woman with a large nose and green skin sitting alone in a cozy coffee shop. The rest of'

[03:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the prompt was the same. And again, here is the full-resolution output. It\'s just as good as anything I\'ve seen. I\'m going to show you a few more examples, but I won\'t get into the detail of all the'

