AUDIO: 'I did it, and yet I showed it to you anyway. Let\'s move on to image-to-video with the Q1 model. You have a couple of choices here. You can just upload one image and let the video happen from that, or you can do a start and end'

[05:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frame. And I\'ve got great examples of both of those. Let\'s just start with using a single image. For many of the examples I\'m going to show you in the image-to-video category, I used Reeve to generate these images because I love how realistic they look and they\'re just'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fantastic to iterate on, which I\'m going to show you examples of when we get into the start and end frame stuff. But the starting image here was this old woman with a cigarette who clearly set her grandson\'s hair on fire. And so the prompt was an old woman pours a bucket'

[06:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of water on his head to put out the fire. And we get this beauty. Now, I didn\'t get the bucket every single time. I had to prompt this a few times to get that bucket to appear out of nowhere, but I was able to prompt it without having a bucket in there or referring to'

[06:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a reference image or anything like that. I also got output like this where she doesn\'t have a bucket and actually seems to be making things worse by tapping more ashes into his hair. And this version here where instead of helping him, she just holds up a second'

